    <chapter>
        <title>XForms Examples</title>

        <abstract>
            <para>This page provides a few examples based on the 
                <ulink url="http://www.agencexml.com/xsltforms">xsltforms</ulink>
            XForms processor, which is included in the eXist distribution. xsltforms implements
            the XForms standard within the browser and is thus easy to integrate. However, eXist will
            also work with other XForms processors like <ulink url="http://www.orbeon.com">Orbeon</ulink>
                or <ulink url="http://chiba-project.org">Chiba</ulink>.</para>
            
            <para>For more information, please have a look at the <ulink url="xforms.xml">documentation</ulink>.</para>
        </abstract>
        
        <section>
            <title>Simple Examples</title>

            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><ulink url="hello.xml">Hello world!</ulink></term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>A very basic example.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><ulink url="hello2.xml">Hello world 2</ulink></term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Another "hello world" which actually stores some data into
                            the db and retrieves it later. Also demonstrates incremental
                            instance loading.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                
            </variablelist>

        </section>
        
